{
  "texts": [
    "A general definition of blockchain is a type of digital ledger that allows you to store any data you want and access it later using the hash value you obtain.",
    "Blockchain and databases can look very similar.",
    "Both technologies actually have the idea of saving data, but while it is possible to add, delete, and change data in a database, it is only possible to add new information to a blockchain.Blockchain was first proposed by Haber and Stornetta in the early 1990s as a mechanism to digitally date, hash, and link data in a chronological manner [4].",
    "Blockchains have undergone enhancements, modifications, and adjustments as the technology has grown and spread.",
    "Now it is viewed as a suitable solution for the identification, registration, distribution, transfer, and tracking of any digital asset since it combines the concepts of \"database\" and \"network\" in computer systems."
  ]
}